	(text "Boost Converter: MT3608\n5V → 12V (adjustable)\nVfb = 0.6V\nVout = 0.6 × (1 + R_FB1/R_FB2)\nR_FB1=187kΩ, R_FB2=10kΩ → 11.8V ≈ 12V\nMax switch current: 2A\nInductor: 22µH (CDRH4D28, Isat≥1.5A)\nD_BOOST: SS14 (1A/40V Schottky, SMA)\nEN pulled HIGH via 100kΩ to VIN (always on)"
		(at 50 10 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000002-text-0000-0000-000000000001")
	)

	(text "Current Source & Bridge\n\nQ1 (Si2302CDS): NMOS current source\n  Gate driven by U1 op-amp output\n  Drain = Node A (laser/dummy anode)\n  Source → Rsense → GND\n  Vgs ≈ U1_out − Rsense_voltage\n\nU1 (TLV2371): R-R op-amp, error amp\n  (+) = VREF (DAC from MSPM0)\n  (−) = Rsense top (Q1 source)\n  Output → Q1 Gate\n  Vcc = LASER_V (5V or 12V)\n\nI_LD = VREF / Rsense\n  Red: Rsense=2.2Ω → Imax=280mA\n  Blue: Rsense=4.7Ω → Imax=120mA"
		(at 140 10 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000002-text-0000-0000-000000000002")
	)

	(text "PWM Bridge (Q2a / Q2b)\n\nBoth NMOS in Si1902DL (SOT-363 dual).\nNOT BSS138DW — insufficient for red laser.\n\nQ2a (laser path):\n  Gate = PWM_LASER (MSPM0 PA8)\n  Drain → LD1 cathode path\n  Source → Node A\n  R_pd_a = 10kΩ to GND (laser OFF on reset)\n\nQ2b (dummy path):\n  Gate = PWM_DUMMY (MSPM0 PA22)\n  Drain → Rdummy/D2 network\n  Source → Node A\n  R_pu_b = 10kΩ to +3.3V (dummy ON on reset)\n\nFail-safe: laser OFF, dummy ON at power-up"
		(at 140 60 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000002-text-0000-0000-000000000003")
	)

	(text "Dummy Load Matching\n\nRed laser (5V/12V, Rsense=2.2Ω):\n  D2 = 1× 1N4148W (0.7V)\n  Rdummy = 8.2Ω (0805, ≥0.5W)\n  Node A voltage match at 230mA:\n  Vdummy = 0.7 + 0.230×8.2 = 2.59V ≈ Vf_LD\n\nBlue laser (12V, Rsense=4.7Ω):\n  D2 = 3× 1N4148W in series (2.1V)\n  Rdummy = 36Ω (0603)\n  Node A match at 87mA:\n  Vdummy = 2.1 + 0.087×36 = 5.23V ≈ Vf_LD"
		(at 140 110 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000002-text-0000-0000-000000000004")
	)

	(text "Laser Diode (LD1, TO-38 socket)\n\nJ_LD: 3-pin 0.1\" header or TO-38 clip\nPin 1 = Anode (→ LASER_V via D1)\nPin 2 = Cathode (red) OR Case/ISO (blue)\nPin 3 = Case/NC (red) OR Cathode (blue)\n\nD1 (BAT54): reverse protection on anode\nMounts between LASER_V and LD anode.\n\nC2 (100nF) + C_bulk (10µF):\nPlace directly at LD anode pad."
		(at 50 100 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000002-text-0000-0000-000000000005")
	)

